<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="360" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1156,444,816]" box="[160,276,444,470]" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,444,470]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1156,444,816]" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">
Carapace transversely ovate, width 1.47 times length (
<figureCitation box="[758,876,479,504]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1182,1205]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1150]" captionTargetId="figure-126@4.[163,1153,142,1150]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Overall dorsal views. (a) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (b) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758418/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Figures 2b</figureCitation>
, and 
<figureCitation box="[934,960,479,504]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">5e</figureCitation>
); surface covered with short, relatively dense pubescence which obscures surface and margins, with numerous long simple setae along margins which partially obscure margin and surface (
<figureCitation box="[168,285,583,608]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[160,225,1182,1205]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1150]" captionTargetId="figure-126@4.[163,1153,142,1150]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Overall dorsal views. (a) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (b) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758418/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Figures 2b</figureCitation>
, and 
<figureCitation box="[343,369,583,608]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">5e</figureCitation>
); anterolateral margin bidentate, with 2 small but clearly defined sharp teeth (
<figureCitation box="[234,340,618,643]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Figure 5e</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of epistome with median lobe flattened, almost level with endostome, lateral margin gently concave (
<figureCitation box="[705,832,653,678]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Figure 5f, g</figureCitation>
); third maxilliped with short, subquadrate ischium, merus quadrate, subdistal margin with low granules (
<figureCitation box="[1030,1151,687,712]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="7.[160,225,1376,1399]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetId="figure-79@7.[163,1153,142,1344]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 5. (a–d) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (e–h) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a, e) dorsal view of carapace; (b, c, f, g) frontal view of cephalothorax; (d, h) left third maxilliped." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758424/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Figures 5h</figureCitation>
, and 
<figureCitation box="[210,236,722,747]" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="9.[160,225,1207,1230]" captionTargetBox="[167,1148,146,1172]" captionTargetId="figure-132@9.[163,1153,142,1176]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 7. (a, d–h) Pseudolitochira maenosonoi sp. nov. (a) holotype male, 4.5 × 2.8 mm, RUMF-ZC -5196, Okinawa. (b) P. pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190, Vanuatu; (c) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a–c) third maxilliped; (d) pleon and telson; (e) whole G1; (f–g) distal tip of G1; H, G2; (a–d) denuded. Scale bars: a–d = 0.5 mm; e, h = 0.2 mm; f, g = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758430/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">7c</figureCitation>
); major chela with fingers about half length of palm (
<figureCitation box="[845,952,722,747]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1591,1614]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. (a, d, f) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190,Vanuatu; (b, c, e, g) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a) chelae; (b) right chela; (c) left chela; (d, e) thoracic sternum and vulvae; (f) right fourth ambulatory leg; (g) right fourth ambulatory leg (merus denuded)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758426/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Figure 6b</figureCitation>
); ambulatory legs with merus and propodus distinctly slenderer (
<figureCitation box="[689,789,757,782]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1591,1614]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. (a, d, f) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190,Vanuatu; (b, c, e, g) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a) chelae; (b) right chela; (c) left chela; (d, e) thoracic sternum and vulvae; (f) right fourth ambulatory leg; (g) right fourth ambulatory leg (merus denuded)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758426/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Figure 6f</figureCitation>
); vulvae large, ovate, positioned close to median part of sternite 6, opening obliquely (
<figureCitation box="[770,875,791,816]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="8.[160,225,1591,1614]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[163,1153,142,1559]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 6. (a, d, f) Pseudolitochira pacifica sp. nov., female, 5.2 × 3.5 mm, ZRC 2017.190,Vanuatu; (b, c, e, g) P. crinita sp. nov., female, 10.0 × 6.8 mm, ZRC 2021.298, Papua New Guinea. (a) chelae; (b) right chela; (c) left chela; (d, e) thoracic sternum and vulvae; (f) right fourth ambulatory leg; (g) right fourth ambulatory leg (merus denuded)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758426" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758426/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Figure 6e</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="360" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1155,863,959]" box="[160,285,863,889]" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,863,889]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1155,863,959]" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">
The name is derived from the Latin for fluffy (
<emphasis box="[676,755,899,924]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="360">crinitus</emphasis>
), alluding to the appearance of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
